doctype html
html
  head
    title Anytime – a JavaScript date and time picker
    link(rel='stylesheet', href='./index.css')
  body
    .main-container
      header.main-header
        h1.main-title Anytime
        h2.subtitle A JS date and time picker
        .splash
          .splash__input
            input(type='text', disabled, placeholder='If not now, when?').js-splash-input
            button.js-splash-button Select a time
          .splash__prose
            ul
              li Say goodbye to jQuery UI!
              li Modularity FTW!
              li Only 4 lines of essential CSS (the rest is up to you)
              li Use with browserify, AMD or standalone
            pre.terminal: code.terminal__content $ npm i --save anytime
      .docs
        h1 Usage

        h2 Browserify

        p This is the recommended and best supported way to use Anytime. Install anytime with npm and require it like so:

        pre.code-sample: code.
          var Picker = require('anytime')
        
        h2 AMD

        p If you’re an AMD user, luckily browserify makes it easy for me to export a UMD version of the module. Go grab the <code>anytime.standalone.js</code> file from the repo.

        pre.code-sample: code
          ='<script src="anytime.standalone.js"></script>'

        h2 Browser Global

        p Yes it’s evil but I’ll let you do it. Here's how to use anytime as a global…

        pre.code-sample: code
          ='<script src="anytime.standalone.js"></script>\n'
          ='<script>\n'
          |   var Picker = window.anytime
          ='\n</script>'

      footer.main-footer
        p Made by Ben Gourley at Clock.

  script(src='./www/js/build.js')
